01/09/2006
ATHENS, Greece -- Economy and Finance Minister George Alogoskoufis said on Thursday (31 August) that all citizens should join the fight against corruption and tax evasion.
Alogoskoufis made the statement at a government meeting with representatives of the largest employers and trade unions in the country.
Interior and Public Administration Minister Prokopis Pavlopoulos added that the cabinet already has tabled necessary anti-corruption legislation to parliament, reiterating there would be zero tolerance for corruption.
For their part, the unions presented their demands for pay raises and reforms in education and healthcare.
(ANA - 31/08/06)
